  <channel>
    <title>Arctic contributor: Peter Mather</title>
    <description>Peter Mather is a photojournalist based in Whitehorse, Yukon. He is a fellow of the International League of Conservation Photographers (iLCP), and is represented by National Geographic Creative. His most recent work has focused on the Gwich’in First Nation people, their connection to the Porcupine caribou herd, and the threats they face from potential development in the calving and nursing grounds of the herd.
</description>
